<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="N" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Nightly1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Nightly,</orth> adj. happening, or acting, or used in the night: <cit><quote>n. linen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 680" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 680</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her n. sorrow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 680" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 680</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>n. tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.132" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 132</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>n. revels,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 5.377" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. V, 377</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to give thee n. visitation,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 75</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the n. owl,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 97</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>give me my n. wearing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 16</bibl></cit>. In <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 68</bibl> Ff <emph>n. colour,</emph> Qq <emph>nighted colour.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>